Certainly! Let's refine the project plan to fit within a 3-month timeframe and include the specified projects along with the AI chatbot development. This plan will start from June 26, 2024, and end on September 26, 2024.

### Phase 1: Planning and Design (June 26, 2024 - July 15, 2024)
- **June 26 - June 28:** Initial meeting to define project scope and objectives
- **June 29 - July 2:** Research and select AI chatbot platform/tools
- **July 3 - July 6:** Design chatbot architecture and user flows
- **July 7 - July 10:** Create detailed project timeline and milestones
- **July 11 - July 15:** Finalize requirements and specifications

### Phase 2: Development and Testing (July 16, 2024 - August 15, 2024)
- **July 16 - July 20:** Set up development environment and integrate chatbot platform
- **July 21 - July 27:** Develop core chatbot functionalities
- **July 28 - August 3:** Implement conversation flows and responses
- **August 4 - August 10:** Integrate AI features (e.g., NLP, machine learning)
- **August 11 - August 15:** Conduct initial testing and debugging

### Phase 3: Integration, Analytics, and Deployment (August 16, 2024 - September 26, 2024)
- **August 16 - August 20:** SharePoint and OBI connection data integration
- **August 21 - August 25:** Develop recommendation engine
- **August 26 - August 30:** Read and analyze data, create analytics
- **August 31 - September 5:** Read documents and answer questions
- **September 6 - September 15:** Build graphs and visualizations based on data
- **September 16 - September 20:** Prepare for deployment (documentation, final tests)
- **September 21 - September 26:** Deploy chatbot and integrated solutions, monitor performance, final review, project closure, and handover

This plan divides the work into three coherent phases, allowing for the development of the AI chatbot alongside the specified projects such as reading documents, data analysis, building a recommendation engine, and integrating with SharePoint and OBI. Adjustments can be made based on specific dependencies and resource availability as the project progresses.
